f(x,y) =\left\{ ce^{(-x-3y)}: 0 <x<\infty, 0<y<\infty \right\}\\0 \ \ \ \ \ \ otherwise 
f
1= \int_0^\infty \int_0^\infty ce^{-x-3y}dxdy  = c \int_0^\infty e^{-x} dx \int_0^\infty e^{-3y}dy  = c \left(-e^{-x}|_0^\infty\right) \left(-e^{-3y}/3|_0^\infty\right)  = c \cdot 1 \cdot \frac{1}{3}, 
c=3
